Package edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.util

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Queue<E>
    Queues are a special, simple type of list where elements are added and removed using a FIFO methodology
    Stack<E>
    Stacks are simple, special types of lists where elements are added and removed from the top
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayList<E>
    Contains information about the ArrayList class
    ArrayQueue<E>
    An ArrayQueue is a queue of elements that functions as an array, using the ArrayList functionality to implement the FIFO queue design
    ArrayStack<E>
    An ArrayStack is a stack that is implemented using functionality from the ArrayList class
    LinkedAbstractList<E>
    A LinkedAbstractList is a list of elements consisting of two pieces of information: the list data and the location of the next element in the list A LinkedAbstractList also has a capacity, which can be altered
    LinkedList<E>
    A generic LinkedList object that extends the AbstractSequentialList class
    LinkedListRecursive<E>
    Creates a LinkedList with recursive functionality
    LinkedQueue<E>
    A LinkedQueue is a queue of elements that functions as an LinkedList, using the LinkedAbstractList functionality to implement the FIFO queue design
    LinkedStack<E>
    A LinkedStack is a stack that is implemented using functionality from the LinkedAbstractList class
